                            <h1>R & D INITIATIVES OF PVKKIT</h1>
						
                    <h3>INITIATIVES FOR STUDENTS</h3>
                    <div class="footer-widget-menu"> 
                        <ul>

                        
						<li >Students are motivated to undertake both in house and industry-based projects.</li>
						<li >Guest lectures, workshops and industrial visits are regularly arranged to focus on thrust areas.</li> 
						<li>Students are encouraged to participate in workshops, seminars, paper presentations and project competitions at the national and international levels.</li>
						<li>Financial assistance for students for publishing and presenting Research papers in peer-reviewed journals and conferences.</li>
						<li>Providing financial assistance to students to develop experimental setups/prototype/working modals of innovative/socially relevant project work.</li> 
						<li>Students are guided and encouraged to prepare and submit research proposals under the student project scheme to external funding agencies on the topic of their project work.</li>
						<li>PVKKIT Innovative Ideas competitions are conducted frequently to inculcate “out of the box” thinking and incubating the best ideas.</li>
						<li>PVKKIT Innovative Ideas Club is started to provide a platform for students to expose, develop and realize their ideas.</li>
						<li>Students are trained in advanced technologies though Oracle academy, NPTEL Online courses/Spoken tutorials etc. to students to enhance their knowledge and skills.</li>
						<li>Virtual lab sessions are conducted to train students so as to help them in learning basic and advanced concepts through remote experimentation.</li> 
					</ul>
